		<legis-type>A BILL</legis-type>
		<official-title>To prohibit certain assistance to the Palestinian Authority.</official-title>
	</form>
	<legis-body>
		<section id="S1" section-type="section-one">
      <enum>1.</enum>
      <header>Short title</header>
			<text display-inline="no-display-inline">This Act may be cited as the
		  <quote>
          <short-title>
            <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="act" value="Stand with Israel Act of 2014" proposed="true">Stand with Israel Act of 2014</cato:entity-ref>
          </short-title>
        </quote>.</text>
    </section>
    <section id="id102b78405f2a452e8e6326284b89b541">
      <enum>2.</enum>
      <header>Prohibition on foreign assistance</header>
      <subsection id="id85A941A632154D47A7AE585BC14072F3">
        <enum>(a)</enum>
        <header>In general</header>
        <text display-inline="yes-display-inline">Except as provided under <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="act" value="Stand with Israel Act of 2014/s:2/ss:b" proposed="true">subsection (b)</cato:entity-ref> and notwithstanding any other  provision of law, no amounts
			 may be obligated or expended to provide any direct
			 United States assistance, loan guarantee, or debt relief to the
			 Palestinian Authority, or any affiliated governing entity or leadership
			 organization.</text>
      </subsection>
      <subsection id="ide357dfe8cccd48f4980ec25e82607e1a">
        <enum>(b)</enum>
        <header>Exception</header>
        <text display-inline="yes-display-inline">The prohibition under <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="act" value="Stand with Israel Act of 2014/s:2/ss:a" proposed="true">subsection (a)</cato:entity-ref> shall have no effect for a fiscal year if the President
			 certifies to <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="federal-body" entity-id="0001">Congress</cato:entity-ref> during that fiscal year 
			 that the Palestinian Authority has—</text>
        <paragraph id="idd7664f7ba81643888e4cd551baa557d1">
          <enum>(1)</enum>
          <text>formally recognized the right of Israel to exist as a Jewish state;</text>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="id2ef0504833e5422aa91a928a2385d37b">
          <enum>(2)</enum>
          <text>publicly recognized the state of Israel;</text>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="id8af61f9803ec4320b3276b9314e62d35">
          <enum>(3)</enum>
          <text>renounced terrorism;</text>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="id143c8f2b86ea496ca05d6ef4d533521e">
          <enum>(4)</enum>
          <text>purged all individuals with terrorist ties from security services;</text>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="id397b7b9309b84bdcb625c81dd139b5df">
          <enum>(5)</enum>
          <text>terminated funding of anti-American and anti-Israel incitement;</text>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="id52241a044d6f4ef783f059d7aadb955a">
          <enum>(6)</enum>
          <text>publicly pledged to not engage in war with Israel; and</text>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="id0163C31002DC405D927253389F4007A2">
          <enum>(7)</enum>
          <text>honored previous diplomatic agreements.</text>
        </paragraph>
      </subsection>
    </section>
    <section id="idf02f16bb690848a4be3cf8f427e7c809">
      <enum>3.</enum>
      <header>Effective date</header>
      <text display-inline="no-display-inline">The prohibition under  <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="act" value="Stand with Israel Act of 2014/s:2" proposed="true">section 2</cato:entity-ref> shall take effect on the later of—</text>
      <paragraph id="id54083E050FDE44138A217F023F4FF4CF">
        <enum>(1)</enum>
        <text display-inline="yes-display-inline">June 1, 2014; or</text>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph id="id6834085BFD0342D9AE93A33FBCC41647">
        <enum>(2)</enum>
        <text display-inline="yes-display-inline">the date of the enactment of this Act.</text>
			</paragraph>
    </section>
